article.description: Josh Nebo scored a career-high 23 points and led five players in double figures as St. Francis (Pa.) defeated Robert Morris 77-57 in a Northeast Conference clash on Thursday night.
article.headline: Nebo scores 23 as St. Francis (Pa.) tops Robert Morris 77-57
article.linkText: Nebo scores 23 as St. Francis (Pa.) tops Robert Morris 77-57
article.story: MOON TOWNSHIP, Pa. -- Josh Nebo scored a career-high 23 points and led five players in double figures as St. Francis (Pa.) defeated Robert Morris 77-57 in a Northeast Conference clash on Thursday night. Nebo made 10 of 12 shots from the floor, grabbed eight rebounds and had seven shot blocks -- also a career best. Isaiah Blackmon and Keith Braxton each scored 14 points for the Red Flash (6-10, 3-2) while Jamaal King and Georgios Angelou pitched in 12 apiece. King opened the second half with a 3-pointer, stretching a six-point halftime lead to 39-30 and Braxton followed with a steal and a layup. With just under six minutes left, Angelou hit a pair of 3-pointers bracketed around a Nebo a basket underneath as St. Francis stretched its lead into double digits for good. Angelo was 4-for-4 from 3-point range. Matty McConnell led the Colonials (6-12, 2-3) with a season-high 15 points.
